  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" M.S. Sanjay versus Indian Bank & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_1_1588_1597','2025INSC177'); ><font size='4'> <strong>M.S. SANJAY<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>INDIAN BANK & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 1 S.C.R. 1588</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 177</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004912025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration An auction was conducted on 31.07.2007 and sale certificate was issued on 30.11.2007. The respondent no.4-guarantor questioned the validity of auction proceedings. In 2019, the High Court declared the auction to be illegal. Whether the High Court failed in noticing jurisdiction. Headnotes&dagger; Constitution of India &ndash; Art. 226 &ndash; Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act (SARFAESI), 2002 &ndash; The respondent no.2 had availed of loan facility from the respondent no.1-Bank &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 29-01-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 1188/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_1_1588_1597','2025INSC177','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_1_1588_1597','2025INSC177','H'); ><i class='